## Build decisions (authoritative â€” implement these)

These override the matching lines in **MP2a** where they differ. Document deltas honestly in the **500-word reflection** (e.g. straight-line sketch pad for clearer matching; PNG-first export; lighter Supabase scope).

| Topic | Decision |
|--------|----------|
| **Audience** | **General public** (curious non-experts), **astronomy hobbyists**, and **artists** â€” low friction, playful, visually rich. Educators/communicators are a welcome secondary audience, not the primary framing. |
| **Drawing** | **Straight-line segments** on a separate **2D sketch pad** (clickâ€“click polyline â†’ SVG polyline). Not freehand curves. |
| **Matching** | On submit: **each polyline vertex** maps to the **nearest visible star** in sky space (approximate; prefer brighter star within a small tie radius, MP1 Felis-style). Lines connect snapped stars on the main map. |
| **Save / export** | **PNG download is must-have** (constellation on star field). **No required Supabase** for full constellation records, share URLs, or retrieve-later flows. |
| **Supabase** | **Optional** â€” if used, **names only**: global uniqueness for AI-generated constellation names (see Naming). Skip Supabase entirely if the demo works with session + classical-name checks only. |
| **Naming** | Per MP2a: user **text description** â†’ **Claude API** via Lovable **edge function**. Keys only in env, never in git. |

**Also must-have (unchanged):** ~9k stars client-side CSV; 2D default + pan/zoom + 3D toggle; mag/size, ci+spect/color, distance; hover `proper` names on **matched** stars only; Roboto Mono / futuristic galaxy look; Lovable deploy + repo data prep.

